<br>
If you just mean to look for the spawn, get a tracker.  Shissar spawns at the top of the temple in the ring of fire, filled with Amygdalan Knights who will HT and kill anybody who goes in unprepared.  However, you can camp a druid or ranger, invis'd, at the safe spot on the west wall and track to the temple from there.  Or, you can have your tracker die outside the portal then run into fear naked, check tracking, then rez them out (naked in case they are unlucky enough to die before rez is cast).  The 2nd method is more practical than hiring a guild druid/ranger to put their char in Fear till next clearing but I've heard of somebody who used his druid alt to 'camp' the mob with his level 51 druid in the safe spot.<br>
<br>
If you want to try to claim the spawn, you will have to clear the zone, or at the very least, the temple mobs and everything that wanders near, and then keep your group at the top of the tower.  He spawns in a room at the top (can't miss it) and is non-agro, so setting up in his room is fine.  However, it's better to do this if you have an idea that shissar will be up soon, because PoF is on a 12-hour(ish) respawn and you won't want to be caught with several members AFK when the plane starts to repop.<br>
<br>
One other method is to use a FD class and either a) feign at the zone-in or safe spot and turn off all text but shouts (when the shissar is up it shouts in the zone every few hours) or b) feign at shissar's spawn point.  The latter is ballsy and very likely to get the monk or necro killed, cuz a missed feign when the temple is spawned means instant death, really no way around it =P however, it does carry the advantage of a visual tab on shissar rather than the less reliable watching for shouts.<br>
<br>
Any way you look at it, it's a pain =\ It took me several weeks of trying just about everything I listed above to track down the thing and kill it... so I wish ya good luck and hope you can get it easier than I did. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87709>Master Rubicant D'Luness - Phantasmist</a><BR>
